name: Drum&BassArena Winter Selection
description: It’s getting cold outside… So warm up with some serious heaters. From peaktime dancefloor shock-outs to gritty neuro hurters, Drum&BassArena Winter Collection 2013 is THE best way to counter this season’s chills. Loaded with 14 exclusives you won’t find anywhere else, it’s out November 24 and you can pre-order it now!

name: Let There Be Bass
description: Entries to our Get Shirty t-shirt design competition were so strong we decided to print up two of them. Last month we unleashed Gwilym Devey’s winning Rowdy Character now we’ve added Luis Barata’s Let There Be Bass t-shirt. Sentiments close to our heart, we’ll be wearing this one with pride. You should, too.

name: Rowdy Looking Character
description:
Gwilym Devey - T-Shirt design competition winner!

Rowdy looking character discharge printed on high quality Stanley Stella black cotton.

Our judges had the following to say in response to picking the winner:

"It instantly spoke to us and has been very well crafted. It shows a sense of individuality from our audience and is a fresh take on the Drum&BassArena style with a cheeky edge!"

name: Drum&BassArena Evolution
description:
Drum&BassArena Evolution: the cutting edge and future sounds of D&B from the scene's biggest artists. From Pendulum and Chase & Status taking basslines to the charts, to the underground sounds of Jubei, Noisia and Rockwell, the scene is thriving across the spectrum. 

So on Evolution we take you from the euphoric vocal-led anthems of Danny Byrd to the technical beats of Icicle's Dreadnaught and back to rowdy dancefloor weapons from Twisted Individual and DJ Hazard. We hit you with the epic panoramic basslines of Loadstar then take it back down with the beautiful orchestral strings of S.P.Y's by your side. 

Nearly 20 years deep, drum & bass has evolved, and is as relevant and as crucial to the dance music scene as ever.

name: Drum&BassArena 2012
description:
Showcasing every shade, every style, every flavour, every formula, Drum&BassArena 2012 is a picture perfect snapshot of where the scene is at right now. 

Brandishing bass music from every coded note, we've crammed two CDs full of the world's most commendable production talent; from Shy FX to High Contrast, Sabre to Sub Focus, Hamilton to Noisia, Stanza to Friction. Founding scene figures b2b hotly tipped emerging players, Drum&BassArena is bulging with material from the scene's most crucial producers.
